</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F43FECE48A751F2FE2BFE5C" lastPageId="270" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="269" pageNumber="270" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F43FECE48A751F2FAB6FE77" blockId="269.[151,1436,151,2035]" lastBlockId="270.[151,1437,151,1954]" lastPageId="270" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="269" pageNumber="270">
Description of Female. Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F43FECD4A9951F2FCB5F906" box="[681,784,1758,1782]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.16" pageId="269" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="11.6">11.6 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible, clypeus, anterior region of face and partly gena testaceous; antenna black, except segments 1–2 testaceous and 6–7 and distal apex of 5 whitish; mesosoma reddish, except propleuron black with dorsal side reddish; petiole and metasoma black; legs reddish, except black spots on protrochanter, protarsus, mesocoxa, meso- and metafemur, meso- and metatibia, meso- and metatarsus. Antenna weakly clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 16:10:86:38:32:24:19:17:15:17. Head (Plate 77E) excavated, dull, reticulate rugose; frontal line complete; clypeus anteriorly emarginated; occipital carina complete, laterally reaching eyes; posterior ocelli touching ccipital carina; temple absent; POL = 4; OL = 4; OOL = 16. Pronotum shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures, with some striae on lateral regions; disc humped; pronotum crossed by two strong transverse impressions; posterior collar very short; pronotal tubercle not reaching tegula. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum dull, reticulate rugose. Notauli incomplete, reaching about 0.75 length of scutum. Propodeum reticulate–rugose, without longitudinal or transverse keels; dorsal surface about as long as posterior surface. Fore wing with two dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein longer than proximal part (11:6). Protarsal segments in following proportions: 34:6:13:25:47. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F40FECE497D5660FE65FE94" box="[333,448,332,356]" captionStart="PLATE 78" captionStartId="271.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,222,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-100@271.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 78. A, B, F. Chelae, holotypes. C. Propodeum, lateral view. D. Profemur and protibia. E. Male genitalia. A. Dryinus hainanensis (from Olmi 1987a). B. D. indianus (from Olmi 1984). C, D. D. indicus, female from China (from Olmi 1984). E. D. indicus, male from India (from Olmi 1984). F. D. indicus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.73 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B, 0.68 mm for C, 0.90 mm for D, 0.25 mm for E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278648/files/figure.png" pageId="270" pageNumber="271">Plate 78A</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and one row of ten lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F40FECE48905643FEB5FE77" box="[160,272,367,391]" captionStart="PLATE 78" captionStartId="271.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,222,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-100@271.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 78. A, B, F. Chelae, holotypes. C. Propodeum, lateral view. D. Profemur and protibia. E. Male genitalia. A. Dryinus hainanensis (from Olmi 1987a). B. D. indianus (from Olmi 1984). C, D. D. indicus, female from China (from Olmi 1984). E. D. indicus, male from India (from Olmi 1984). F. D. indicus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.73 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B, 0.68 mm for C, 0.90 mm for D, 0.25 mm for E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278648/files/figure.png" pageId="270" pageNumber="271">Plate 78A</figureCitation>
) with two rows of about 27 lamellae; distal apex with about 20 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F40FECE48F756B8FE2BFE5C" blockId="270.[151,1437,151,1954]" box="[199,398,404,428]" pageId="270" pageNumber="271">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
